article.description: — Donovan Dent's 23 points helped New Mexico defeat UCSB 84-61 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Dent's 23 lead New Mexico past UCSB 84-61
article.linkText: Dent's 23 lead New Mexico past UCSB 84-61
article.story: ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. -- — Donovan Dent's 23 points helped New Mexico defeat UCSB 84-61 on Wednesday night. Dent also added eight assists for the Lobos (8-1). JT Toppin scored 18 points and added three blocks. Tru Washington had 17 points and went 7 of 11 from the field. The Lobos picked up their seventh straight victory. Ajay Mitchell led the way for the Gauchos (4-3) with 22 points, five assists and two steals. UCSB also got 18 points from Yohan Traore. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
